
What is HTML5?
What is <!DOCTYPE>? is it necessary to use in HTML5?
List out the new features of HTML5?
  
List out the advantages of HTML5?

List out new HTML5 APIs?
  //geolocation, drag and drop, local storage, application cache, web workers, SSE
  
What are the types of semantic elements introduced in HTML5?
  //semantic elements, form elements, multimedia elements and graphic elements
  
What are semantic elements?
  //Semantic HTML elements clearly describe it’s meaning in a human and machine readable way. 
    A semantic element clearly describes its meaning to both the browser and the developer.
    Elements such as <header>, <footer> and <article> are all considered semantic because they accurately describe 
      the purpose of the element and the type of content that is inside them.
    The are very helpful for pure efficiency and SEO.
    
What are the list of new semantic elements?
  //article,section,header,footer,aside,nav, figure,figcaption, main, mark , meter, summary, time
  
What are the grpahic elements available in html5?
  //svg,canvas
  
What are the multimedia elements available in html5?
  //audio,vedio,embed,source,track
  
What are the new form elements available in html5?
  //output, datalist
  
What is the difference between SVG and canvas?
  //SVG - scalable vector graphics - vector based(XML) , while CANVAS is raster based(pixel)
  SVG is Multiple graphical elements, which become the part of the DOM, where as CANVAS is Single HTML element similar to <img> in behavior.
  SVG can be modified using script and CSS, while CANVAS can only be modified through script.
  SVG has Better scalability — can be printed with high quality at any resolution(zoom out wont have any impact) while 
      CANVAS has Poor scalability — not suitable for printing on higher resolution(zoom out will break the image quality)
  SVG gives better performance with smaller number of objects or larger surface. CANVAS gives better performance with smaller surface or larger number of objects.
  


  
    
